Test sorting with various amounts of undefined types and polymorphism.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope Tsort1:
  output o1 content list of (optional of money, integer)
  output o2 content list of (optional of money, integer)
  output o3 content list of (optional of money, integer)
  output o4 content list of (optional of money, integer)
  output o5 content list of (optional of money, integer)

scope Tsort1:
  definition o1 equals
    sort [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)] in increasing order
  definition o2 equals
    sort all (a, n) among [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)] in increasing order of a
  definition o3 equals
    sort all (a, n) among [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)] in increasing order of n
  definition o4 equals
    sort all (a, n) among [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)] in increasing order of []
  definition o5 equals
    let bla equals
      sort all (a, n) among [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)] in increasing order of a
    in
    []
```


```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope Tsort1
┌─[RESULT]─ Tsort1 ─
│ o1 = [(Absent, 2); (Absent, 3); (Absent, 4)]
│ o2 = [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)]
│ o3 = [(Absent, 2); (Absent, 3); (Absent, 4)]
│ o4 = [(Absent, 4); (Absent, 2); (Absent, 3)]
│ o5 = []
└─
```
